BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 748 Tm (- Dockerize backend deployment for consistency) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 733 Tm (- Use Terraform for infra management) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 718 Tm (- Replace long-lived AWS keys with GitHub OIDC + IAM roles) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 703 Tm (- Add CloudFront invalidation after S3 deploys) Tj ET
BT /F2 14 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 680 Tm (Part 4: Debugging Scenario) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 652 Tm (Problem flow:) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 629 Tm (`Driver App -> Django API -> S3 -> Celery -> Bedrock -> PostgreSQL`) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 606 Tm (I would debug in the same order as the request path instead of jumping straight to Celery or) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 591 Tm (Bedrock.) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 568 Tm (Step-by-step Approach) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 543 Tm (1. Reproduce the issue with one known image and one known user.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 528 Tm (Why: it is much easier to trace one request end to end than to reason from noisy production) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 513 Tm (traffic.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 490 Tm (2. Check whether the request reaches Django.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 475 Tm (Why: if the API never receives it, the issue is in the client, auth, or network path.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 460 Tm (Tools: Django logs, nginx/ALB logs, CloudWatch.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 437 Tm (3. Verify the S3 upload step.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 422 Tm (Why: if the object never lands in S3, the bug is before Celery and Bedrock.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 407 Tm (Tools: S3 console, boto3 error logs, CloudWatch.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 384 Tm (4. Confirm Celery task creation and worker pickup.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 369 Tm (Why: if S3 succeeded but no task was queued, the issue is in app logic or broker flow.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 354 Tm (Tools: Celery worker logs, Flower, Redis queue inspection.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 331 Tm (5. Inspect the Bedrock call.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 316 Tm (Why: sometimes the upload succeeds and the actual failure is in downstream inference.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 301 Tm (Tools: CloudWatch, worker logs, Bedrock invocation errors.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 278 Tm (6. Check PostgreSQL writeback.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 263 Tm (Why: the system may look like an upload failure when the final DB update is the real issue.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 248 Tm (Tools: Django logs, PostgreSQL logs, targeted SQL checks.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 225 Tm (7. Compare one failing case with one successful case.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 210 Tm (Why: patterns like file type, file size, or environment mismatch often show up quickly.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 72 187 Tm (8. Add temporary tracing across each step if the issue is intermittent.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 172 Tm (Why: step-level visibility reduces guesswork.) Tj ET
BT /F2 14 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 149 Tm (Conclusion) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 121 Tm (I focused on simple, scalable, and cost-efficient solutions that are realistic for a small) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 106 Tm (engineering team to build and operate. The common theme across all four parts is to keep the) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 91 Tm (design easy to reason about, make failure handling explicit, and avoid over-engineering too) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 54 76 Tm (early.) Tj ET
endstream
